HEADWORD: devastating
<hw>devastating</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>highly critical;
making light of; <as>as, a <ex>devastating</ex> portrait of human
folly</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> annihilating, withering.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>causing or capable of causing complete destruction;
<as>as, a <ex>devastating</ex> hurricane</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> annihilative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Devastation</ent>⟦br⟧
